  "why": "The paper provides partial diagnostic insight into the discovered failures: it characterizes how failures depend on the types and number of input transformations (showing sensitivity to spatial transformations and that robustness degrades as the transformation space grows), compares different fitness metrics (loss-based vs. neuron-coverage) and selection metrics (loss-based vs. classification-based) for finding failure-inducing variants, and analyzes point-wise robustness to guide selective augmentation. However, it does not trace failures to underlying model vulnerabilities (e.g., dataset bias, corrupted labels, or learned spurious features) or provide root-cause explanations that would indicate how to fix specific model weaknesses beyond improved augmentation. Therefore it meets the criterion for Medium.",
